label: cites work
description: citation from one creative or scholarly work to another

label: series ordinal
description: position of an item in its parent series (most frequently a 1-based index), generally to be used as a qualifier (different from "rank" defined as a class, and from "ranking" defined as a property for evaluating a quality).

label: author name string

label: instance of
description: that class of which this subject is a particular example and member; different from P279 (subclass of); for example: K2 is an instance of mountain; volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform)

label: stated in
description: to be used in the references field to refer to the information document or database in which a claim is made; for qualifiers use P805; for the type of document in which a claim is made use P3865

label: retrieved
description: date or point in time that information was retrieved from a database or website (for use in online sources)

label: reference URL
description: should be used for Internet URLs as references. Use "Wikimedia import URL" (P4656) for imports from WMF sites

label: title

label: publication date
description: date or point in time when a work was first published or released

label: published in
description: larger work that a given work was published in, like a book, journal or music album

label: page(s)
description: page number of source referenced for statement. Note "column(s)" (P3903) and "folio(s)" (P7416) for other numbering systems

label: volume
description: volume of a book or music release in a collection/series or a published collection of journal issues in a serial publication

label: issue
description: issue of a newspaper, a scientific journal or magazine for reference purpose

label: apparent magnitude
description: measurement of the brightness of an astronomic object, as seen from the Earth

label: astronomical filter
description: passband used to isolate particular sections of the electromagnetic spectrum

label: author
description: main creator(s) of a written work (use on works, not humans); use P2093 (author name string) when Wikidata item is unknown or does not exist

label: DOI
description: serial code used to uniquely identify digital objects like academic papers (use upper case letters only)

label: main subject
description: primary topic of a work (see also P180: depicts)

label: catalog code
description: catalog name of an object, use with qualifier P972

label: catalog
description: catalog for the item, or, as a qualifier of P528 – catalog for which the 'catalog code' is valid

label: language of work or name
description: language associated with this creative work (such as books, shows, songs, broadcasts or websites) or a name (for persons use "native language" (P103) and "languages spoken, written or signed" (P1412))

label: object named as
description: use as qualifier to indicate how the object's value was given in the source

label: country
description: sovereign state that this item is in (not to be used for human beings)

label: located in the administrative territorial entity
description: the item is located on the territory of the following administrative entity. Use P276 for specifying locations that are non-administrative places and for items about events. Use P1382 if the item falls only partially into the administrative entity.

label: point in time
description: date something took place, existed or a statement was true; for providing time use the "refine date" property (P4241)

label: occupation
description: occupation of a person; see also "field of work" (Property:P101), "position held" (Property:P39)

label: coordinate location
description: geocoordinates of the subject. For Earth, please note that only WGS84 coordinating system is supported at the moment

label: start time
description: time an entity begins to exist or a statement starts being valid

label: sex or gender
description: sex or gender identity of human or animal. For human: male, female, non-binary, intersex, transgender female, transgender male, agender, etc. For animal: male organism, female organism. Groups of same gender use subclass of (P279)

label: determination method
description: how a value is determined, or the standard by which it is declared

label: based on heuristic
description: indicates that the property value is determined based on some heuristic (Q201413); to be used as source

label: epoch
description: epoch of an astronomical object coordinate

label: right ascension
description: astronomical equivalent of longitude

label: declination
description: astronomical equivalent of latitude

label: given name
description: first name or another given name of this person; values used with the property should not link disambiguations nor family names

label: constellation
description: the area of the celestial sphere of which the subject is a part (from a scientific standpoint, not an astrological one)

label: PMCID
description: identifier for a scientific work issued by PubMed Central (without "PMC" prefix)

label: date of birth
description: date on which the subject was born

label: Wikimedia import URL

label: parallax

label: imported from Wikimedia project

label: Commons category
description: name of the Wikimedia Commons category containing files related to this item (without the prefix "Category:")

label: image

label: right ascension component of proper motion

label: declination component of proper motion
description: the value μᵟ as a component of the proper motion of a star

label: country of citizenship
description: the object is a country that recognizes the subject as its citizen

label: family name
description: part of full name of person

label: end time
description: moment when an entity ceases to exist or a statement stops being valid

label: part of
description: object of which the subject is a part (if this subject is already part of object A which is a part of object B, then please only make the subject part of object A), inverse property of "has part" (P527, see also "has parts of the class" (P2670))

label: subclass of

label: radial velocity
description: component of the object's velocity that points in the direction of the radius connecting the object and the point

label: subject named as

label: ortholog
description: orthologous gene in another species (use with 'species' qualifier)

label: found in taxon
description: the taxon in which the item can be found

label: full work available at URL
description: URL of a web page containing the full body of this item

label: copyright status
description: copyright status for intellectual creations like works of art, publications, software, etc.

label: parent taxon
description: closest parent taxon of the taxon in question

label: taxon name
description: correct scientific name of a taxon (according to the reference given)

label: taxon rank
description: level in a taxonomic hierarchy

label: distance from Earth
description: estimated distance to astronomical objects

label: place of birth
description: most specific known (e.g. city instead of country, or hospital instead of city) birth location of a person, animal or fictional character

label: date of death
description: date on which the subject died

label: location
description: location of the object, structure or event. In the case of an administrative entity as containing item use P131. For statistical entities use P8138. In the case of a geographic entity use P706. Use P7153 for locations associated with the object

label: inception
description: time when an entity begins to exist; for date of official opening use P1619

label: exact match
description: URL used to link two items or properties, indicating a high degree of confidence that the concepts can be used interchangeably

label: category combines topics
description: this category combines (intersects) these two or more topics

label: educated at
description: educational institution attended by subject

label: Elo rating
description: quantitative measure of one's game-playing ability, particularly in classical chess

label: chromosome
description: chromosome on which an entity is localized

label: population
description: number of people inhabiting the place; number of people of subject

label: short name
description: short name of a place, organisation, person, journal, wikidata property, etc. Used by some Wikipedia templates.

label: languages spoken, written or signed
description: language(s) that a person or a people speaks, writes or signs, including the native language(s)

label: collection
description: art, museum, archival, or bibliographic collection the subject is part of

label: heritage designation
description: heritage designation of a cultural or natural site

label: number of pages
description: number of pages in an edition of a written work; see allowed units constraint for valid values to use for units in conjunction with a number

label: has part(s)
description: part of this subject; inverse property of "part of" (P361). See also "has parts of the class" (P2670).

label: described by source
description: work where this item is described

label: sport
description: sport that the subject participates or participated in or is associated with

label: copyright license
description: license under which this copyrighted work is released

label: located in time zone
description: time zone for this item

label: postal code
description: identifier assigned by postal authorities for the subject area or building

label: official website URL
description: URL of the official page of an item (current or former). Usage: If a listed URL no longer points to the official website, do not remove it, but see the "Hijacked or dead websites" section of the Talk page

label: employer
description: person or organization for which the subject works or worked

label: made from material
description: material the subject or the object is made of or derived from (do not confuse with P10672 which is used for processes)

label: genre
description: creative work's genre or an artist's field of work (P101). Use main subject (P921) to relate creative works to their topic

label: street address
description: full street address where subject is located. Include building number, city/locality, post code, but not country; use also P669 if the street has its own separate item

label: ORCID iD
description: identifier for a person

label: criterion used
description: property by which a distinction or classification is made

label: file format
description: file format, compression type, or ontology used in a file

label: official name
description: official name of the subject in its official language(s)

label: filename in archive
description: qualifier and referencing property to identify the specific file within a compressed archive that is relevant to a statement

label: child
description: subject has object as child. Do not use for stepchildren—use "relative" (P1038), qualified with "type of kinship" (P1039)

label: country of origin
description: country of origin of this item (creative work, food, phrase, product, etc.)

label: ISNI
description: International Standard Name Identifier for an identity. Starting with 0000.

label: pronunciation
description: lexeme form pronunciation, usually identical to the form's representation, but may include other indicators (pronunciation audio/IPA text may be attached as qualifiers, and duplicate values are OK if more than one pronunciation exists)

label: member of sports team
description: sports teams or clubs that the subject represents or represented

label: taxon author
description: the author(s) that (optionally) may be cited with the scientific name

label: applies to part
description: part, aspect, or form of the item to which the claim applies

label: inventory number
description: identifier for a physical object or a set of physical objects in a collection

label: position held
description: subject currently or formerly holds the object position or public office

label: object has role
description: (qualifier) role or generic identity of the value of a statement ("object") in the context of that statement; for the role of the item the statement is on ("subject"), use P2868

label: award received
description: award or recognition received by a person, organization or creative work

label: cast member
description: actor in the subject production [use "character role" (P453) and/or "name of the character role" (P4633) as qualifiers] [use "voice actor" (P725) for voice-only role]

label: mass
description: mass (in colloquial usage also known as weight) of the item

label: curator
description: content specialist responsible for this collection or exhibition

label: genomic assembly
description: specify the genome assembly on which the feature is placed

label: reason for deprecated rank
description: qualifier to indicate why a particular statement should have deprecated rank

label: follows
description: immediately prior item in a series of which the subject is a part, preferably use as qualifier of P179 [if the subject has replaced the preceding item, e.g. political offices, use "replaces" (P1365)]

label: applies to jurisdiction
description: the item (institution, law, public office, public register...) or statement belongs to or has power over or applies to the value (a territorial jurisdiction: a country, state, municipality, ...)

label: followed by
description: immediately following item in a series of which the subject is a part, preferably use as qualifier of P179 [if the subject has been replaced, e.g. political offices, use "replaced by" (P1366)]

label: elevation above sea level
description: height of the item (geographical object) as measured relative to sea level

label: place of death
description: most specific known (e.g. city instead of country, or hospital instead of city) death location of a person, animal or fictional character

label: chemical formula
description: description of chemical compound giving element symbols and counts

label: InChIKey
description: A hashed version of the full standard InChI - designed to create an identifier that encodes structural information and can also be practically used in web searching.

label: canonical SMILES
description: Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry Specification (canonical format)

label: InChI
description: International Chemical Identifier

label: creator
description: maker of this creative work or other object (where no more specific property exists)

label: year of publication of scientific name for taxon
description: year when this taxon was formally described (for animals); year when this taxon name was formally established (for plants)

label: redshift
description: the redshift measure of an astronomical object

label: height
description: vertical length of an entity

label: last update
description: date a reference was modified, revised, or updated

label: PubChem CID
description: identifier from database of chemical molecules and their activities in biological assays (Compound ID number)

label: molecular function
description: represents gene ontology function annotations

label: biological process
description: is involved in the biological process

label: contains the administrative territorial entity
description: (list of) direct subdivisions of an administrative territorial entity

label: ADS bibcode
description: bibcode in the Astrophysics Data System

label: described at URL
description: item is described at the following URL

label: genomic end
description: genomic ending coordinate of the biological sequence (e.g. a gene)

label: genomic start
description: genomic starting coordinate of the biological sequence (e.g. a gene)

label: strand orientation
description: orientation of gene on double stranded DNA molecule

label: father
description: male parent of the subject. For stepfather, use "stepparent" (P3448)

label: on focus list of Wikimedia project
description: property to indicate that an item is of particular interest for a Wikimedia project. This property does not add notability. Items should not be created with this property if they are not notable for Wikidata. See also P6104, P972, P2354.

label: spectral class
description: spectral class of an astronomical object

label: width
description: width of an object

label: native label
description: label for the items in their official language (P37) or their original language (P364)

label: owned by
description: owner of the subject

label: ranking
description: subject's ordinal position as qualitatively evaluated relative to other members of a group

label: encoded by
description: the gene that encodes some gene product

label: encodes
description: the product of a gene (protein or RNA)

label: field of work
description: specialization of a person or organization; see P106 for the occupation

label: significant event
description: significant or notable events associated with the subject

label: different from
description: item that is different from another item, with which it may be confused

label: CAS Registry Number
description: identifier for a chemical substance or compound per Chemical Abstract Service's Registry database

label: part of the series
description: series which contains the subject

label: academic degree
description: academic degree that the person holds

label: inferred from
description: statement added based on related statement found on the following item, not the entity described by the item (to be used in a reference field)

label: cell component
description: component of the cell in which this item is present

label: expressed in
description: gene or protein is expressed during a specific condition/cell cycle/process/form

label: of
description: (This property is being deprecated, see details at WD:P642) qualifier stating that a statement applies within the scope of a particular item

label: category contains
description: category contains elements that are instances of this item

label: depicts
description: entity visually depicted in an image, literarily described in a work, or otherwise incorporated into an audiovisual or other medium; see also P921, 'main subject'

label: DSSTOX compound identifier
description: identifier of a compound in America's Environmental Protection Agency chemical database "DSSTOX"

label: number of points/goals/set scored
description: goals / points scored in a match or an event used as qualifier to the participant. Use P1358 for league points.

label: shares border with
description: countries or administrative subdivisions, of equal level, that this item borders, either by land or water. A single common point is enough.

label: participant in
description: event in which a person or organization was/is a participant; inverse of P710 or P1923

label: historic county
description: traditional, geographical division of Great Britain and Ireland

label: spouse
description: the subject has the object as their spouse (husband, wife, partner, etc.). Use "unmarried partner" (P451) for non-married companions

label: valid in period
description: time period when a statement is valid

label: maintained by WikiProject
description: WikiProject that maintains this property, item, or linked pages. If the WikiProject is hosted outside of Wikidata, define the scope using the qualifier "of (P642)"

label: software version identifier
description: numeric or nominal identifier of a version of a software program or file format, current or past

label: effective temperature
description: the temperature of a black body that would emit the same total amount of electromagnetic radiation as measured star or planet

label: participant
description: person, group of people or organization (object) that actively takes/took part in an event or process (subject). Preferably qualify with "object has role" (P3831). Use P1923 for participants that are teams.

label: operator
description: person, profession, or organization that operates the equipment, facility, or service

label: taxon common name
description: common or vernacular name of a biological taxon

label: China administrative division code
description: identifier for administrative divisions of People's Republic of China (with spaces)

label: number of matches played/races/starts
description: matches or games a player or a team played during an event. Also a total number of matches a player officially appeared in during the whole career.

label: writing system
description: alphabet, character set or other system of writing used by a language, word, or text, supported by a typeface

label: UMLS CUI
description: NLM Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) controlled biomedical vocabulary unique identifier

label: area
description: area occupied by an object

label: category's main topic

label: topic's main category
description: main Wikimedia category

label: online access status
description: property or qualifier for an ID property indicating whether linked content is directly readable online

label: mother
description: female parent of the subject. For stepmother, use "stepparent" (P3448)

label: social media followers
description: number of subscribers on a particular social media website (use as main statement only; see P3744 instead for qualifier). Qualify with "point in time" and property for account. For Twitter, use numeric id.

label: name in native language
description: name of a person in their native language

label: ITIS TSN
description: identifier for a taxon in the Integrated Taxonomic Information System

label: U.S. National Archives Identifier
description: identifier for the United States National Archives and Records Administration's online catalog

label: surface gravity
description: gravitational acceleration experienced at the equator of an astronomical body surface

label: statement is subject of
description: (qualifying) item that describes the relation identified in this statement

label: level of description
description: position of the unit of description in the hierarchy of the fonds

label: publisher
description: organization or person responsible for publishing books, periodicals, printed music, podcasts, games or software

label: legal citation of this text
description: legal citation of legislation or a court decision

label: describes a project that uses
description: essential component or tool that was used in the project described in this output

label: place of publication
description: geographical place of publication of the edition (use 1st edition when referring to works)

label: maintained by
description: person or organization in charge of keeping the subject (for instance an infrastructure) in functioning order

label: member of political party
description: the political party of which a person is or has been a member or otherwise affiliated

label: performer
description: actor, musician, band or other performer associated with this role or musical work

label: parliamentary term
description: term of a parliament or any deliberative assembly

label: grammatical gender
description: grammatical gender of the word

label: member of
description: organization, club or musical group to which the subject belongs. Do not use for membership in ethnic or social groups, nor for holding a political position, such as a member of parliament (use P39 for that)

label: headquarters location
description: city or town, where an organization's headquarters is or has been situated. Use P276 qualifier for specific building

label: religion or worldview
description: religion of a person, organization or religious building, or associated with this subject

label: NCBI locus tag
description: unique gene identifier that can be used for any species of organism

label: collection or exhibition size
description: number of items in a collection or exhibition

label: subject has role
description: role/generic identity of the item ("subject"), also in the context of a statement. For the role of the value of the statement ("object"), use P3831 ("object has role"). For acting roles, use P453 ("character role"). For persons, use P39.

label: named after

label: number of participants
description: number of participants of an event, e.g. people or groups of people that take part in the event (NO units)

label: sibling
description: the subject and the object have at least one common parent (brother, sister, etc. including half-siblings); use "relative" (P1038) for siblings-in-law (brother-in-law, sister-in-law, etc.) and step-siblings (step-brothers, step-sisters, etc.)

label: form of creative work
description: structure of a creative work

label: electoral district
description: electoral district this person is representing, or of the office that is being contested. Use as qualifier for "position held" (P39) or "office contested" (P541) or "candidacy in election" (P3602)

label: work location
description: location where persons or organisations were actively participating in employment, business or other work

label: original language of film or TV show

label: female population

label: OS grid reference

label: position played on team / speciality
description: position or specialism of a player on a team

label: copyright status as a creator
description: states if the body of work published during the lifetime of this creator is still copyrighted or in the public domain

label: male population
description: number of male people inhabiting the place; number of male people of subject

label: use restriction status
description: status of any use restrictions on the object, collection, or materials

label: access restriction status
description: status of any access restrictions on the object, collection, or materials. Indicates whether the material is available to the general public or not.

label: X username

label: National Heritage List for England number
description: number on the National Heritage List for England

label: Soundex

label: director

label: type of variable star
description: type of star

label: isomeric SMILES
description: dedicated SMILES for isomer

label: latest date
description: latest possible time that something could have occurred. Use as qualifier for other date properties

label: has works in the collection
description: collection that has works of this person or organisation (use archives at [P485] for archives)

label: study type

label: version type
description: type of version (qualifier for P348, software version), e.g. alpha, beta, stable

label: record label

label: has facility

label: length

label: minimum age

label: doctoral student

label: pronunciation variety
description: qualifier for IPA transcription (P898), pronunciation audio (P443) or spoken text audio (P989) to indicate the associated spoken language variant

label: earliest date
description: earliest date at which an event could have happened. Use as qualifier for other date properties

label: distribution format

label: residence

label: number of subscribers

label: said to be the same as

label: name

label: dissolved, abolished or demolished date

label: sport number
